Package book

Interface Summary
TradeProcessor Interface that defines the functionality needed to “execute” the actual trades between Tradable objects in this book side.
 

Class Summary
ProductBook The ProductBook object maintains the Buy and Sell sides of a stock’s “book”.
ProductBookSide Maintains the content of one side (Buy or Sell) of a Stock (product) “book”.
ProductService This class is the Facade to the entities that make up the Products (Stocks), and the Product Books (“booked” tradables on the Buy and Sell side).
TradeProcessorFactory Creates TradeProcessor objects for different allocation algorithms
TradeProcessorPriceTimeImpl This Tradeprocessor implementer contains the functionality needed to “execute” actual trades between Tradable objects in this book side using a price-time algorithm
 

Enum Summary
ProductBookSide.BookSide Hold valid values for the side that the current ProductBookSide represents.
TradeProcessor.AllocationStrategy Trades will be executed based on their price and the time they were submitted to they system.
